29/06/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police arrested a man Monday (June 28th) suspected of organising the weekend attack on a police station in Bugojno that claimed the life of one police officer. 
Naser Palislamovic, 37, is allegedly an associate of Haris Causevic, who has confessed to activating the explosive device. 
Police have already detained several other people for questioning. 
(Nezavisne Novine, RTRS, BHRT, Dnevnik.ba, Dnevni Avaz - 28/06/10)
